ity, the police are wasting their time on this nonsense.\n\nMan, the UK is a joke\n\n", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 12}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsn9vPNJ", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 300, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8660941, "raw_content": "", "author": "Milward", "created": 1780653925112, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "acesfull", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "media.scored.co", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsn9vPNJ.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://media.scored.co/post/PUL5SP5nivHm.jpeg", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/LGhuP7qEgGtyLcu5.jpeg", "width": 275, "content-type": "jpeg", "height": 183}], "blurhash": "U9DR?7OY0K~Cx^In0f?G00IUM{R*tS%2-UI;", "full_resolution": [183, 275]}, "title": "South Carolina! On Tuesday June 9th dump Lindsey Graham.\n\nGraham is toxic for America!", "last_comment_created": 1780687079638, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 8, "score_up": 300, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsnCAYK2", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 27, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8662372, "raw_content": "\"While receiving zero votes in a random sample of 24,000 with 30% support is mathematically impossible (probability $\\approx 0$), election batches are not random samples.\n\nExample: If a candidate has 30% support statewide but only 0.5% support in a specific liberal precinct, and a batch contains 24,000 ballots from that precinct (or a cluster of similar precincts), receiving 0 or very few votes is the expected outcome, not an anomaly. \nConclusion: The phenomenon is a result of California's decentralized counting method, where results are reported by county and often by batch type (mail vs. in-person), creating temporary statistical skews that resolve as more diverse batches from different regions are counted.\"", "author": "CommieCucker", "created": 1780700937636, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "CommieCucker", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "oh that makes sense (BULLSHIT, i can understand a very low number, but not FUCKING ZERO)", "last_comment_created": 1780707104578, "content": "<p>&quot;While receiving zero votes in a random sample of 24,000 with 30% support is mathematically impossible (probability $\\approx 0$), election batches are not random samples.</p>\n<p>Example: If a candidate has 30% support statewide but only 0.5% support in a specific liberal precinct, and a batch contains 24,000 ballots from that precinct (or a cluster of similar precincts), receiving 0 or very few votes is the expected outcome, not an anomaly.\nConclusion: The phenomenon is a result of California's decentralized counting method, where results are reported by county and often by batch type (mail vs. in-person), creating temporary statistical skews that resolve as more diverse batches from different regions are counted.&quot;</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 4, "score_up": 27, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2062916616476565878", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsnB2Qqr", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 106, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8661475, "raw_content": "", "author": "DCSucks", "created": 1780674086458, "profile_picture": "HROqPiS20z4h", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "TrumpMagaNoBama", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsnB2Qqr.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/RadioGenoa/status/2062916616476565878?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Back to Africa", "last_comment_created": 1780705835096, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 15, "score_up": 106, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 23, "created": 1780672623000, "id": "2062916616476565878", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/2062916582280437760/pu/img/B5eRGyWLvWOE_YVg.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/ext_tw_video/2062916582280437760/pu/pl/7hhCwhWilI5ZzUXu.m3u8", "aspectRatio": [184, 135], "heightRatio": 73, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/ext_tw_video/2062916582280437760/pu/vid/avc1/368x270/jLiPMmEuLD0CjyoK.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1925910917482426368/vXAnSPXI_normal.jpg", "displayName": "R